 found to have larger depth\ncompared to the disk/bar,which supports the existence of an inner halo for the\nLMC.On the other hand, the estimated depths for the halo(RR Lyrae stars)and\ndisk are found to be similar,for the SMC bar region. Thus,increased depth and\nenhanced stellar as well as HI density near the optical center suggests that\nthe SMC may have a bulge.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 25 Sep 2008 10:25:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 2 Feb 2009 14:34:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-07-21"}
